The paper deals with the IEEE 802.11ax amendment, which is a wireless networking standard. The paper focuses on the Spatial Reuse (SR) operation, which is a technique to improve the performance of WLANs in dense environments. This involves maximizing the reutilization of the medium by increasing the number of parallel transmissions. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves analytical modeling and simulation-driven analysis, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses the challenges and limitations of the SR operation, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
